  "verbGlossary": {
    "ACCESS": "{target} provides elevated or otherwise unreachable work access to {source}, enabling trades to perform installation or finishing tasks at height or in confined areas.",
    "APPLIED": "{source} is spread, adhered, or coated onto {target} as a protective or finished surface layer.",
    "APPLIES": "Labor resource spreads, adheres, or coats material onto {target} to create a protective or finished surface layer.",
    "BOLTED": "{source} is mechanically fastened with bolts to form {target} connection, transferring structural loads between members.",
    "BUILT": "{source} is fabricated and assembled on-site or in a shop to form the finished building element.",
    "BUILT INTO": "{source} is incorporated as a structural or functional component within {target} during its assembly.",
    "COMPACTS": "{source} densifies soil or aggregate beneath or around {target} to achieve the required bearing capacity or subgrade density.",
    "DECKED": "{source} is laid as metal deck panels across {target} framing to serve as a form and reinforcement for the concrete slab.",
    "DISTRIBUTES": "{source} moves and stages bulk materials to the point of installation so trades can incorporate them into {target}.",
    "DRIVES": "{source} forces piles or deep foundation elements into the ground to the specified bearing depth or resistance.",
    "EMBEDDED": "{source} is placed within {target} before concrete is poured, becoming permanently cast in place to provide tensile reinforcement.",
    "ERECTED AS": "{source} is lifted, positioned, and connected to form the structural building element as part of the steel or metal framework.",
    "ERECTS": "Labor resource lifts, aligns, and permanently connects structural members to assemble {target} in its final position.",
    "EXCAVATES": "{target} removes earth, rock, or other material to create the void or trench required for {source}.",
    "FABRICATED": "{source} is cut, shaped, and welded in a shop or on-site to produce the custom building element before installation.",
    "FIREPROOFS": "{target} applies fire-resistive material to {source} to achieve the required hourly fire rating.",
    "FORMED": "{source} is bent, shaped, or configured to create the profile of {target} prior to permanent attachment.",
    "FORMS": "{source} or material constructs temporary formwork that defines the shape of {target} until the concrete cures.",
    "FRAMED": "{source} is assembled into the stud or structural framework that constitutes {target}.",
    "FRAMES": "{source} or wood studs to construct the structural framework of {target}.",
    "GLAZED": "{source} is set into the frame or opening of {target} as a transparent or translucent panel.",
    "GRADES": "{source} levels and shapes the earth surface to the specified elevation and slope required by {target}.",
    "HANGS": "{source} or panel material to the framing to form the surface of {target}.",
    "HAULS": "{target} transports excavated or fill material to or from {source} location.",
    "HUNG": "{source} is fastened to framing as sheet or panel stock to form the finished surface of {target}.",
    "INSTALLED": "{source} is permanently placed, fastened, or connected in its final position to become a functional part of {target}.",
    "INSTALLS": "Labor resource permanently places, fastens, or connects components to create or complete {target}.",
    "LAID": "{source} is set in place on a prepared surface to form the finished floor or paved building element.",
    "LAID AS": "{source} is set course by course with mortar to construct the masonry building element.",
    "LAYS": "{source} or piece by piece on a prepared surface to construct {target}.",
    "LIFTS": "{source} hoists {target} or its components from staging to the point of installation at elevation.",
    "OPERATES": "{source} or paving operations that create or support {target}.",
    "PIPED": "{source} is assembled as a piping network to form the distribution or collection system of {target}.",
    "PLACED": "{source} is deposited and finished in its final location to form {target} surface or base.",
    "PLACED IN": "{source} is poured or deposited into formwork or an excavation to form the mass of {target}.",
    "PLACES": "{source} or equipment pours, deposits, and finishes material to form {target} in its final location.",
    "PULLED": "{source} is drawn through conduit or raceway to provide the wiring or cabling that makes {target} functional.",
    "PULLS": "{source} through conduit or raceway to complete the wiring of {target}.",
    "PUMPS": "{source} conveys concrete under pressure through hoses or pipes to deliver it to {target} location, typically at height or distance from the truck.",
